(# Media Controller - Full Working Reference) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Generated: 2026-03-28) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 1\) Project Purpose) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This project runs a web-controlled media slideshow system for Raspberry Pi \(or Linux desktop\).) Tj
T*
(It provides:) Tj
T*
(- A Flask web dashboard to upload/delete media and control playback.) Tj
T*
(- A slideshow engine that plays photos and videos fullscreen.) Tj
T*
(- Safe process and file handling \(PID file, pending delete queue\).) Tj
T*
(- Shop-ready deployment using a systemd service script.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2\) High-Level Runtime Flow) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. `python app.py` starts Flask web server.) Tj
T*
(2. User opens `http://<device-ip>:5000`.) Tj
T*
(3. User presses `START`.) Tj
T*
(4. Flask starts `python slideshow.py` in a separate process.) Tj
T*
(5. `slideshow.py` loops through `photos/` and `videos/`.) Tj
T*
(6. User can `STOP`, upload media, delete media, and change interval.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
